@startuml
title WOTS+ hash chain for one base-w digit (w = 16, lg_w = 4)
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

rectangle "sk_i\n(secret start)" as SK
rectangle "F(sk_i)" as C1
rectangle "..." as C2
rectangle "chain value at\nposition = digit\n(the signature)" as SIG
rectangle "F^(w-1)(sk_i)\n(public chain end)" as PK

SK -right-> C1 : F
C1 -right-> C2 : F
C2 -right-> SIG : F (digit times)
SIG -right-> PK : F (w-1-digit times)

note bottom of SIG
  Signing reveals the chain element at
  height = message digit. Verifier hashes
  it forward to the public end.
  A checksum over all digits stops an
  attacker advancing chains to forge.
end note

note right of PK
  T_l compresses every chain end
  into the WOTS+ public key.
  One-time only: two signatures leak forgery.
end note
@enduml
